              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Prolog is a very old language. It was first created before modular software development was the standing religion and it was not designed for this degree of modularity. Modules as a concept had to be retrofitted to a language design which almost, but not quite, actively resisted being made modular."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "maybe that's why a lot of tutorials and books do not seem to cover the subject"
              }
